The White House Press Secretary, Jay Carney, along with Deputy National Security Advisors Ben Rhodes and Mike Froman, held a press briefing at the G20 summit in Cannes, France. The briefing covered a range of topics including the eurozone crisis, the global economic agenda, and the situation in Greece. Froman emphasized the need for the G20 to focus on the global economy and the importance of implementing the plan to deal with the eurozone crisis. Rhodes discussed the discussions between President Obama and European leaders, particularly regarding the Greek situation and the need for a comprehensive plan to stabilize the eurozone. Froman also mentioned the importance of growth and job creation in the G20 agenda and the role of the IMF in supporting the eurozone crisis. The briefing also touched on the Iranian nuclear program and the upcoming bilateral events honoring the service of American and French service members in the Libya operation.